# ARCHITECTURE CORRECTION (verify-don't-blindly-build): in the LOCKED retrieve-and-verify design, Ring-3
# stores a content-addressable POINTER (id), not a lossy gist. On recall we unbind -> id -> fetch the
# VERBATIM Ring-2 tensor from Optane -> inject THAT. So a correct recall has ZERO fidelity loss by
# construction (same bytes as a direct inject). The directive's 'gist-PPL vs verbatim-PPL' delta would be
# ~0 (trivial/misleading) or require the convicted lossy-gist Path B. The real loss has three axes:

## (1) HIT fidelity = LOSSLESS (the verify re-injects exact bytes)
  base       [g4-ppl] SP PPL=4.6665 (report-only; set SP_PPL_ORACLE to gate) n_scored=42 n_ctx=84 chunks=1
  HIT        [g4-ppl] SP PPL=4.6665 (report-only; set SP_PPL_ORACLE to gate) n_scored=42 n_ctx=84 chunks=1
  -> HIT deflection = (4.6665-4.6665)/4.6665 = +0.000%  (correct id -> verbatim ep_wiki, NPOS=16)

## (2) the lossy axis = CAPACITY MISS (a step function, caught by the gate)
  MISS       [g4-ppl] SP PPL=5.0417 (report-only; set SP_PPL_ORACLE to gate) n_scored=42 n_ctx=84 chunks=1
  -> MISS deflection = (5.0417-4.6665)/4.6665 = +8.04%  (wrong id -> foreign ep_toy, NPOS=16)
  -> +8.04% >> the 2.0% deflection gate ⇒ a capacity miss is FLAGGED and O(1)-rewound, NOT silently corrupting.
  -> recoverable-info loss is BINARY: 0 on hit, total on miss; governed by recall@1(N) from G-R3-BIND.

## (3) promotion budget (pinned from the G-R3-BIND capacity curve @ D=1024)
  -> recall@1 = 1.000 up to N=32 (lossless recall); recall@5>=0.90 to N=64.
  -> BUDGET: consolidate <= 32 episodes per Ring-3 superposition vector for lossless recall;
     beyond that, misses are caught by the 2% gate (degrade-safe, never silent corruption).

## (4) latency shear (two-stage retrieve-and-verify vs a resident hit)
  -> unbind + cleanup: 71 us per recall @ D=1024 N=32 (negligible vs the model forward);
     dominant added cost = ONE Optane ReadFile of the episode (the existing Ring-2 backend); inject/score unchanged.

